@hammy0520 @Heirtrigger Correct-a-Mundo. 

People WANT this to run like GME is. Hell, every ticker on ST wants their ticker to move like GME or AMC. The reason these tickers were targeted was their high shorted share volume. $FCEL does not have that. We have shorts, but not at the rate of these other guys. Their really wouldn’t be a, “stick to the man,” in FCEL’s case, because not that many people would be out of the money for it to have the same impact. 

The goal for $FCEL is for people to lock up their shares from being borrowed (put a Limit Sell at $100 for all your shares with no expiry for example) and longs need to quit worry about “profit taking” and either add or hold. Profit taking does nothing if you think this stock is going to the moon, like me. You’re not doing anyone any favors by taking profits. Unless you need them to pay your bills (a whole different situation, I feel for y’all, we’ve all been there) then just set your final exit and hold long. Bullish
